    Scope and Contents
The Faculty Senate Academic Standards Committee (Series II ) records (1979-83) consists of minutes, working papers, memos regarding grading, probation policies and communication skills, and program proposals and deficiencies.  The Academic Standards Committee develops and reviews policies concerning academic standards of the university including admission statements, grading systems and degree requirements.   The Curriculum Committee and the Academic Standards Committee were joined in April 1983, to become the Curriculm &amp; Acaemic Standards Committee.  
  
